More on chickens
----------------
I found it ironic that the last paragraph of a recent posting [WEST NILE
VIRUS SURVEILLANCE - USA (25) reads...The total number of West Nile
positive specimens for New York State this year is 202 birds, 87 mosquito
pools, 1 sentinel chicken and 3 human cases. This suggests to me that
humans are serving as an effective sentinel for the chickens. However, we
have seen in previous postings that the Canadians have set up a chicken
perimeter. If dead crows and other birds are such effective indicators,
perhaps they may consider shifting their efforts while there is still time.
--
Rick Lehtinen
<lehtinenfamily@home.com>
